<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>Privacy | PanorOmics</title>

<style>

body{
  margin:0;
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,sans-serif;
  line-height:1.75;
}

.privacy-wrapper{
  max-width:980px;
  margin:0 auto;
  padding:48px 22px 36px;
}

.privacy-kicker{
  color:#3b82f6;
  font-size:.72rem;
  letter-spacing:.24em;
  font-weight:700;
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

.privacy-title{
  font-size:2.35rem;
  line-height:.98;
  letter-spacing:-0.05em;
  margin-bottom:22px;
}

.privacy-title span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.privacy-intro{
  color:#cbd5e1;
  max-width:760px;
  font-size:.92rem;
  margin-bottom:34px;
}

.privacy-section{
  margin-bottom:30px;
  padding-bottom:20px;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
}

.privacy-section h2{
  font-size:1.35rem;
  margin-bottom:16px;
  color:white;
}

.privacy-section p{
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.94rem;
}

.privacy-footer{
  margin-top:26px;
  padding-top:24px;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
  color:#64748b;
  font-size:.82rem;
  text-align:center;
}

a{
  color:#60a5fa;
  text-decoration:none;
}

a:hover{
  color:white;
}

@media(max-width:768px){

  .privacy-wrapper{
    padding:42px 18px 28px;
  }

  .privacy-title{
    font-size:2rem;
  }

}

</style>

</head>

<body>

<div class="privacy-wrapper">

  <div class="privacy-kicker">
    PRIVACY & DATA RESPONSIBILITY
  </div>

  <h1 class="privacy-title">
    Responsible Privacy for <span>Omics Sciences</span>
  </h1>

  <p class="privacy-intro">
    PanorOmics recognizes the importance of privacy,
    scientific integrity, ethical data stewardship,
    and responsible computational biology across omics sciences,
    artificial intelligence, biotechnology, and translational research.
  </p>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>Information Collection</h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics may collect limited technical,
      educational, or communication-related information
      necessary to improve institutional services,
      scientific resources, and educational experiences.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>Scientific & Educational Use</h2>

    <p>
      Information shared with PanorOmics is intended
      to support scientific communication,
      educational engagement, institutional collaboration,
      and responsible omics sciences initiatives.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>Data Stewardship</h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics supports responsible stewardship of
      genomic, molecular, computational,
      and research-associated data through principles of
      scientific rigor, ethical responsibility,
      and transparency.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>AI & Computational Systems</h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics recognizes the evolving role of
      artificial intelligence and computational systems
      in omics sciences and supports ethical,
      transparent, and scientifically responsible implementation.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>External Links</h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics may provide links to external
      scientific resources, educational organizations,
      journals, institutions, or collaborative platforms.
      External websites maintain independent policies
      and governance practices.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="privacy-section">

    <h2>Contact</h2>

    <p>
      Questions regarding privacy,
      institutional responsibility,
      or scientific governance may be directed to:
      <a href="/contact">PanorOmics Contact</a>
    </p>

  </section>

  <div class="privacy-footer">
    PanorOmics © 2026 • Pittsburgh, PA • USA
  </div>

</div>

</body>

</html>
